<div class="c230_120"> 
<div id="v230.120.1"><span class="H7892 s">A Song</span><span class="H4609 s"> of degrees</span><span class="H6869 s">. In my distress</span><span class="H7121 s"> I cried</span><span class="H3068 s"> unto the LORD</span><span class="H6030 s">, and he heard</span> me.</div> 
<div id="v230.120.2"><span class="H5337 s">Deliver</span><span class="H5315 s"> my soul</span><span class="H3068 s">, O LORD</span><span class="H8267 s">, from lying</span><span class="H8193 s"> lips</span><span class="H7423 s">, <i>and</i> from a deceitful</span><span class="H3956 s"> tongue</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.120.3"><span class="H5414 s">What shall be given</span><span class="H3254 s"> unto thee? or what shall be done</span><span class="H7423 s"> unto thee, thou false</span><span class="H3956 s"> tongue</span>? <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (What shall be given…: or, What shall the deceitful tongue give unto thee? or, what shall is profit thee?) (done: Heb. added)</span></div> 
<div id="v230.120.4"><span class="H8150 s">Sharp</span><span class="H2671 s"> arrows</span><span class="H1368 s"> of the mighty</span><span class="H1513 s">, with coals</span><span class="H7574 s"> of juniper</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Sharp…: or, It is as the sharp arrows of the mighty man, with coals of juniper)</span></div> 
<div id="v230.120.5"><span class="H190 s">Woe</span><span class="H1481 s"> is me, that I sojourn</span><span class="H4902 s"> in Mesech</span><span class="H7931 s">, <i>that</i> I dwell</span><span class="H168 s"> in the tents</span><span class="H6938 s"> of Kedar</span>!</div> 
<div id="v230.120.6"><span class="H5315 s">My soul</span><span class="H7227 s"> hath long</span><span class="H7931 s"> dwelt</span><span class="H8130 s"> with him that hateth</span><span class="H7965 s"> peace</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.120.7"><span class="H7965 s">I <i>am for</i> peace</span><span class="H1696 s">: but when I speak</span><span class="H4421 s">, they <i>are</i> for war</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (for peace: or, a man of peace)</span></div></div> 
